The Code Arch

Formal definition
-----------------

The position of AoC is what used to be called 'helper Arch'. His, and
his helper's task, is to aid coding Wizards with problems that either
can't be solved by reading the documentation or examples.  He should
also be responsible for keeping the examples up to date and write new
as modifications to the mudlib or gamedriver requires. In as much as
his time allows he should also keep an eye on the game log and aid the
domains in keeping the game running smoothly.

Amendments
----------

This Archwizard Position is not currently utilized.
